WHITE RIVER – Police spokesman Col Mtsholi Bhembe said police are looking for the family or acquaintances of a woman who was found by the road on Tuesday. He said the victim was estimated to be in her early 30’s  and was wearing a red and black blouse, red jeans with a brown belt and she had long braids (hairstyle). Anyone who has a missing family member or may know this person is requested to contact WO Timothy Shabangu at 071-881-8682 or SAPS White River at 013-750-0888.